Completeness:
- [x] Minimum test case added
- [x] Device, system and user firmware versions stated

If WKP pin is held HIGH on deep sleep wake, RTC alarm and future LOW to HIGH transition on WKP will not wake device.

Tested on 0.6.0 and 0.6.1-rc.2.

- If you short WKP to 3V3 and let the device sleep, you can observe:
  - remove short before 5 seconds expires without accidentally glitching the WKP LOW/HIGH and the RTC alarm will wake the device.
  - remove short before 5 seconds expires without accidentally glitching the WKP LOW/HIGH and short WKP back to 3V3 the device will wake.
  - leave short for > 5 seconds and RTC alarm will fail to wake device, also removing the short and reapplying (LOW to HIGH transition on WKP) will not wake the device.
  - Only affected when RTC is used, does not occur with `System.sleep(SLEEP_MODE_DEEP);`

See community post here: https://community.particle.io/t/alarm-issue-with-sleep-mode-deep-after-wkp-pin-event/30018
>There is an interesting Note in the STM32F205xx Reference Manual which states the following:

>Note: An additional wakeup event is detected if the WKUP pin is enabled (by setting the EWUP bit) when the WKUP pin level is already high. (see PWR_CSR register description).

```c
void setup()
{
    pinMode(D7, OUTPUT);
    digitalWrite(D7, HIGH);
    delay(1000);
    System.sleep(SLEEP_MODE_DEEP, 5);
}

void loop()
{
}
```

